children.subject: Nope! This is intended for beginners with no previous experience, from any major.
Hi, I'm an incoming freshman, this DeCal sounds great. Are there any prereqs for enrolling in this DeCal?

history.content:
The Web Design DeCal is still on, and will be taught remotely for Fall 2020! Class will be over Zoom with lectures on Tuesdays 7–8:30pm and lab time Thursdays 7–8pm. Everything will be recorded. Enrollment info will be up on our website, http://wdd.io/, by the first week of the semester.

We're currently looking for TAs to join the team – if you have webdev and/or design experience and are interested in helping us teach this completely introductory course, we encourage you to apply at http://wdd.io/go/ta-app by this Saturday, July 25. No need to have taken the decal before (I didn't)! Besides answering questions during class, TAs attend remote staff meetings on Thursdays before classtime, 6:30–7pm, host their own office hours, and help revise our curriculum. You can also get 2 PNP units for this.

Feel free to post follow-ups if you have any questions about the course or the TA app!
